snippet.title: 5sf's Comments of the Week - 3/26 - 3/30
snippet.description:
For today's extra-large comments revue, we're in front of a famous place in France that I've always wanted to go to...that is, until someone decides to spill beer on the greenscreen. Featuring a bizarre showdown with a cheeseburger, extreme butt-chin closeups and more.

RIP Edd Gould, you are gone but not forgotten. http://www.youtube.com/user/eddsworld

snippet.title: 5secondfilms Week In Review #179
snippet.description: Wounded with a broken limp an old settler must foley his way off a desert island to be reunited with the dignified lady he left back home.

snippet.title: 5sf Behind The Scenes - More Dignified Ladies - Outtakes
snippet.description:
Delightful outtakes from "A Dignified Lady"

Original Film: http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=lcQlpCYAppw

snippet.title: A Dignified Lady
snippet.description: Falling out of a time portal can do weird things to your hand-eye coordination. Or at least that's the excuse she gave.

snippet.title: Joe Goes For Help
snippet.description: In his final days, Joe did in fact send for help by attaching several strands of hair to a circling vulture that got too close. Undeterred, the vulture simply bathed in the ocean to get the hair off, when an orca emerged from beneath it and swallowed it whole. It was then that Joe realized the ocean sucks.

snippet.title: Sound FXXX
snippet.description: Foley guys are unsung heroes. They do all manner of exhausting tests with dead bodies just to discover what kinds of squishes they'll later need to mimic with groceries.

snippet.title: Settlers Of The Old Interstate
snippet.description: They came from miles around, looking for a fresh start. First came the gas stations, then the AM/PMs, then the combination KFCs/Dunkin Donuts. Soon there was talk of building an overpass, and on the other side, tract housing developments. There was a new world waiting for the settlers, but it would not be won overnight.

snippet.title: Wrap It Up
snippet.description: The money you save on your water bill just from a broken arm is insane. That is, assuming the paramedics find you in under 5 minutes.

snippet.title: 5sf's Comments of the Week - 3/19 - 3/24
snippet.description: More questions! More comments! More beer!

snippet.title: 5secondfilms Week In Review #178
snippet.description: A study in yearbook signatures capture the nostalgia behind moon conspiracies and dog dance moves

snippet.title: Do The Tractor Beam
snippet.description: The Reverse Thrust is a classic escape maneuver, but can result in all manner of wildlife, power tools and passersby being inexorably drawn to your rhythmic thrusting. Sometimes it can spell your doom just as much as succumbing to the power of a group's thrust pile-up.

snippet.title: Dog Days For Pauly P.
snippet.description: Pauly's spiritual pilgrimage to Temecula (which, due to a miscommunication, he thought was Mecca for at least three straight peyote-drenched weeks) resulted in the hostile takeover of a pet store chain and, with it, a whole crop of new ads.

snippet.title: Whither Thou How Now, The Man In The Moon
snippet.description: Worse yet, think of how the poor owner of midwestern family theme park Moonworld will feel about this sobering news.

snippet.title: Captured
snippet.description: With the new Canon lenses, every shot is a bird's-eye shot.

snippet.title: Yearbook Signatures
snippet.description:
As you can tell, Billy gained a lot of confidence with women that senior year, mostly from winning the Mathletes Nationals, but partly from a three-week, hooker-filled bender in Cancun with his cousin Marco.

snippet.title: 5sf's Comments of the Week - 3/12 - 3/16
snippet.description:
Special thanks to @alexhanly for this week's awesome background!

And usual thanks to all of you for your continued support and feedback. Here's us cackling about it for three and a half minutes.

Seriously though, next week we're going to answer philosophical questions only. Bonus points if they pertain to the 5sf in question.

snippet.title: Week in Review #177
snippet.description: Tummy filled with delicious skirt steaks, Kelsey got a 3D tattoo, danced the Macarena, fell in love with a beehive, and started a grunge band. She immediately regretted all of these things.

snippet.title: My Grunge Band's Playing At A Coffeeshop
snippet.description: Worse still, his 'zine was getting too expensive to photocopy. He could've let more people know via beeper, but he spent all his money on Doc Martens.

snippet.title: The Sting Of Love
snippet.description: I know what a lot of you are thinking: "How could he cheat on Olivia?" That's because you've never made love to an entire hive of bees in your life. You're young, you'll understand one day.

snippet.title: The Spy Who Twirled Me
snippet.description: When he was younger, his father recorded over his instructional dance tapes with a TV presentation of "Dirty Harry." His mean streak either comes out of a misplaced sense of vengeance or an inability to grasp that dance moves don't suddenly end in murder.

snippet.title: 3D Tattoo
snippet.description: The Bleeding Knees Club went on to have a band meeting. They decided that knives stuck in the back are definitely not cool, and that the police should be alerted about an attempted murder.

snippet.title: Skirt Steak
snippet.description: It's not really an effective mutant ability for her, especially when compared to good old-fashioned Misplaced Anger and a gun.

snippet.title: 5sf's Comments of the Week - 3/5 - 3/9
snippet.description:
To cap off what y'all so affectionately dubbed "Man Week" at 5sf, we decided to have an all-male edition of the Week in Comments Review! By that, we mean Kelsey and Olivia just weren't around and we had beer too early in the morning. Anyway, enjoy this video! It's our hilarious parody of "House of Flying Daggers!"

And come check out our online store! http://store.5secondfilms.com/

snippet.title: 5secondfilms Week In Review #176
snippet.description: An exploding fart assassination staged by the CIA backfires when John McClane is held prisoner on his own lawn by Andrew W.K.

snippet.title: What Makes Andrew W.K. Rock So Hard?
snippet.description: Don't ask him how much he loves death metal. There will be no survivors.

snippet.title: Old Man Peterson's Lawn
snippet.description: He didn't have time to debate them on whether a top-down, bird's-eye view of his lawn would still indicate that they were "on" it, because he had to go clean off the accident he made in his britches.

snippet.title: Die Easy
snippet.description: Soooo, the Nakatomi Corporation went bankrupt, the members of Asian Dawn were inexplicably released from prison, and his ex-wife's respect for him plummeted even further. On the plus side, he finally scratched that hard-to-reach itch that was bugging him.

snippet.title: Paul Was In The C.I.A.
snippet.description: Right now, as this 5-second film unspools on home computers across America, 36 dormant agents just uncontrollably dismantled their cats.

snippet.title: Identical Problems
snippet.description: He was on his way to a barbecue in the park when his friends saw it happen from across the field. He tried laughing it off and changing the subject, but one of his friends sat him down on a pack of ice on top of the cooler, and told it to him straight. "You've got to find your twin and beat the crap out of him once and for all," they said somberly. "Be the man your father wanted one of you to be."

snippet.description:
This week, join us under the sea (courtesy of @Spectre_X's suggestion), where the jokes are wetter, the comments are better and there's fresh crab at the buffet line nonstop! Also featuring a super-special kill reel starring our very own Michael Rousselet!

snippet.title: 5secondfilms Week In Review #175
snippet.description: A man is taken aback when his brahs confess to him that Weird Owl will be in a 5sf in order to help their money laundry scheme make it rain.

snippet.title: Makin' It Rain
snippet.description: They have a water park in heaven that doubles as a rainmaker for Earth, which is a fantastic tax incentive. So, that's not even actually his job.

snippet.title: Laundry Day
snippet.description: That money, incidentally, is going towards a suit made entirely out of dollar bills, which he will then splatter with blood at a violent club shootout, which will necessitate laundering after all. But let's not get ahead of ourselves.

snippet.title: Weird Owl
snippet.description: I am Jack's half-eaten mouse. I am Jack's hollowed-out oak tree.

snippet.title: My Two Brahs
snippet.description: Some brahs are there to support you. Some brahs lie just to make you think you're better than you are. And some brahs just break down when you need them the most.

snippet.title: Taken
snippet.description: You know how the story goes. Boy meets girl. Boy packs up and moves to a new apartment. Boy loses girl amidst the hustle and bustle. Boy frequents restaurants, coffee shops and bars to try and find girl. Boy meets other girls. Boy finds girl again. Boy is crazy.

snippet.title: 5secondfilms Week In Review #174
snippet.description: Oscar Week 2012! The Oscars are threatened when an atheist attacks the Best Animal Performance nominees because they were too good playing War Whores!

snippet.title: War Whores
snippet.description: Oscar Week comes to a close once more, with this four-hanky epic about that terrible, bloody invention of man that tears countries apart, pits man against animal, and shatters families. Of course, we are talking about whores.

snippet.title: Best Animal Performance
snippet.description: Andy Serkis was nominated the next year, three times over, for playing all of the leads in the gritty reboot of Homeward Bound. However, he still lost to the only other nominee -- Squeegee the Dolphin for her stunning, heartfelt work in Karate Dolphin and the Case of the Phantom Tortoise. He became so enraged that he dumped out his goodie bag on Nick Nolte and was violently ejected from the theater.

snippet.title: Extremely Loud and Incredibly Close
snippet.description: Step 1: Decide to win an Oscar for Best Screenplay (Original or Adapted). Step 2: Thumb through National Tragedies Weekly for inspiration. Step 4: Profit. (Step 3 is to write the thing, which we feel sorta goes without saying)

snippet.title: The Atheist
snippet.description:
Nothing underscores the emptiness of the void that surrounds our meaningless universe quite like tap dancing and pencil thin mustaches.

snippet.description: Even worse were the twitter responses afterward. @Hugo said "Dammmmn, I'd let Chris Brown beat me out for an award anytime." Just a sad day in general.

snippet.description: A Serial Killer is forced to take a lie detector test in regards to the beaver slaughter but its a false alarm because he's just a sexy cowboy

The Snitches, Bitches & Soggy Britches Gang inevitably cleans up on strip poker night. Their willingness to start each game off with a considerable handicap strikes fear into other players' well-clothed hearts.

snippet.title: False Alarm
snippet.description: Her disappointment with being denied a chance to create a new, better baby was only matched by her boundless stupidity.

snippet.title: Widower's Lament
snippet.description: The sound of the dam bursting is still fresh in his memory. The crack of the branches. The high-pitched screams. The tails whapping against the rushing water. The sound of Kelsey asking why he was crying on his knees.

snippet.title: True Love
snippet.description: The lie detector technician also served at the wedding as the priest. He was sweating profusely throughout the ceremony, but the bride and her matching Glock .357 looked radiant.

snippet.title: Serial Killer On The Loose!
snippet.description: Nobody wants to read "Dead, Overweight Body Found in Silver Spring Again" in their morning paper. That's sure to get buried in the back pages, next to the stories about missing cats.
